8. Trend Analysis of Common Crime Types Over the Years

In[29]:
# Analyze trends for selected crime types
selected_crimes = ['Murder', 'Assault on women', 'Kidnapping and Abduction']

plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
for crime in selected_crimes:
    sns.lineplot(data=df.groupby('Year')[crime].sum().reset_index(), x='Year', y=crime, marker='o', label=crime)

plt.title('Trend of Common Crime Types Against SCs Over the Years')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Crime Counts')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Bar width
bar_width = 0.4
years = df_acts["Year"]
index = np.arange(len(years))

# Plotting both acts together
plt.bar(index, df_acts["Prevention of atrocities (POA) Act"], bar_width, label='POA Act', color='blue')
plt.bar(index, df_acts["Protection of Civil Rights (PCR) Act"], bar_width, bottom=df_acts["Prevention of atrocities (POA) Act"], label='PCR Act', color='red')

# Adding labels and title
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Total Crime Counts')
plt.title('Total Crimes Under POA Act and PCR Act by Year')
plt.xticks(index, years, rotation=90)
plt.legend(title='Crime Acts')

# Display the plot
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
In[57]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Plotting the POA Act and PCR Act trends over the years
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))

# Enhanced line plot for each act with markers
sns.lineplot(data=df_acts, x="Year", y="Prevention of atrocities (POA) Act", 
             marker='o', label="POA Act", color='blue', linewidth=2.5, markersize=10)

sns.lineplot(data=df_acts, x="Year", y="Protection of Civil Rights (PCR) Act", 
             marker='s', label="PCR Act", color='red', linewidth=2.5, markersize=10)

# Adding titles and labels with custom fonts and sizes
plt.title('Trends of Crimes under POA Act and PCR Act Over the Years', fontsize=22, fontweight='bold', color='darkslategray')
plt.xlabel('Year', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold', color='darkslategray')
plt.ylabel('Total Crime Counts', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold', color='darkslategray')

# Customizing the legend
plt.legend(title='Crime Acts', fontsize=12, title_fontsize=14, frameon=True)

# Annotate the maximum points
max_poa = df_acts['Prevention of atrocities (POA) Act'].max()
max_poa_year = df_acts[df_acts['Prevention of atrocities (POA) Act'] == max_poa]['Year'].values[0]
plt.annotate(f'Max: {max_poa}', 
             xy=(max_poa_year, max_poa), 
             xytext=(max_poa_year + 1, max_poa + 10),
             arrowprops=dict(facecolor='blue', arrowstyle='->'),
             fontsize=12, color='blue', fontweight='bold')

max_pcr = df_acts['Protection of Civil Rights (PCR) Act'].max()
max_pcr_year = df_acts[df_acts['Protection of Civil Rights (PCR) Act'] == max_pcr]['Year'].values[0]
plt.annotate(f'Max: {max_pcr}', 
             xy=(max_pcr_year, max_pcr), 
             xytext=(max_pcr_year - 2, max_pcr + 20),
             arrowprops=dict(facecolor='red', arrowstyle='->'),
             fontsize=12, color='red', fontweight='bold')

# Improved grid visibility
plt.grid(visible=True, linestyle='-', linewidth=0.9, alpha=0.9)

# Tight layout for better spacing
plt.tight_layout()

# Show plot
plt.show()
